# Documentation language

**Default language for all project documentation is English.**

## Write in English

- `docs/` (except `docs/es/`)
- `research/`
- `validation/`, `upstream/docs/`
- `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- Comments in install scripts meant for maintainers
- Commit messages and PR descriptions for this repo

## Spanish (explicit exceptions only)

- User-facing guides mirrored under `docs/es/` (e.g. `INSTALACION.md`, `VALIDACION-FW.md`)
- Files explicitly named `*.es.md` or `README.es.md`
- Chat with the user may stay in Spanish per user preference; **files on disk stay English by default**

## Bilingual pattern

```
docs/INSTALL.md          ← English (canonical)
docs/es/INSTALACION.md   ← Spanish mirror
research/track-A-….md    ← English
```

When adding a new doc, create the English version first. Add a Spanish mirror under `docs/es/` only when there is already a bilingual pair for that topic.

## Research and reports

Investigation notes, failure reports, and track docs in `research/` must be **English**, not Spanish.

If legacy content is in Spanish, prefer translating or replacing with an English file on the next edit; link EN/ES pairs in the index when both exist.
